d1 = ("THE GODFATHER\nSYNOPSIS A mafia family struggles to establish its supremacy in the United States after World War II. An assassination attempt on the boss Vito Corleone incapacitated and forced Michael Sonny to take over the business.\nAUTHOR:Mario Puzo\nAVAILABLE IN: Amazon Prime Video")
d2 = ("SCHINDLER'S LIST\nSYNOPSIS: The German Oskar Schindler saw Jewish labor as a cheap and viable solution for profiting from business during the war. With his strong influence within the Nazi party, it was easy to get permits and open a factory. What might seem like the attitude of a not very kind man turned into one of the greatest love affairs for life in history, as this German gave up all his fortune to save the lives of more than a thousand Jews in the middle of the fight against German extermination \nAUTHOR: Thomas Keneally\nAVAILABLE IN: Google Play, Amazon Prime Video and Youtube")
d3 = ("A DREAM OF FREEDOM\nSYNOPSIS: After a few years in prison Stickan comes out and tries to re-adjust to society. He is approached by his old prison buddy Janne who is full of ideas on how to get money without having to work.\nAUTHOR: Diane McWhorter\nAVAILABLE IN: Globoplay, Amazon Prime Video, Telecine, Youtube and Google Play")
d4 = ("LIFE IS BEAUTIFUL\nSYNOPSIS: During World War II in Italy, the Jew Guido and his son Giosué are taken to a Nazi concentration camp. Away from the woman, he has to use his imagination to make the boy believe that they are participating in a great game, in order to protect him from the terror and violence that surround them.\nAUTHOR: Roberto Benigni / Vincenzo Cerami\nAVAILABLE IN: Amazon Prime Video and Youtube")
d5 = ("THE SHAWSHNK REDEMPTION\nSYNOPSIS: In 1946, Andy Dufresne (Tim Robbins), a young and successful banker, has his life radically changed when he is convicted of a crime he never committed, the murder of his wife and her lover. He is sent to a prison that is every inmate's nightmare, Shawshank State Penitentiary, Maine. There he will serve his life sentence. Andy will soon be introduced to Warden Norton (Bob Gunton), the corrupt and ruthless prison guard who uses the Bible as a weapon of control, and Captain Byron Hadley (Clancy Brown) who treats inmates like animals. Andy befriends Ellis Boyd Redding (Morgan Freeman), a prisoner who has served 20 years and controls the institution's black market.\nAUTHOR: Stephen King\nAVAILABLE IN: Netflix, HBO Max, Amazon Prime Video, Youtube and Google Play")
d6 = ("MEN OF HONOR\nSYNOPSIS:Carl Brashear, a young black man, joins the US Navy in his 50s, a time when racism prevailed in the country. The young man faces prejudice from his white peers and his instructor, but his courage and determination earn him the respect of all.\nAUTHOR: Scott Marshall Smith\nAVAILABLE IN: Amazon Prime Video, Star+, Google Play and Youtube")
d7 = ("FIGTH CLUB\nSYNOPSIS:A depressed man suffering from insomnia meets a strange salesman named Tyler Durden and finds himself living in a dirty house after his perfect apartment is destroyed. The duo form a club with strict rules where men fight. The perfect partnership is compromised when one woman, Marla, attracts Tyl's attention.\nAUTHOR: Chuck Palahniuk\nAVAILABLE IN: Netflix, Star+, Amazon Prime Video and Telecine")
d8 = ("SAVING PRIVATE RYAN\nSYNOPSIS:Upon landing in Normandy, on June 6, 1944, Captain Miller receives the mission of commanding a group of the Second Battalion to rescue soldier James Ryan, the youngest of four brothers, three of whom died in combat. On orders from Chief George C. Marshall, they must search for the soldier and ensure he returns home alive.\nAUTHOR: Robert Rodat\nAVAILABLE IN: Netflix, HBO Max, Globoplay, Amazon Prime Video, Youtube and Google Play")
d9 = ("GLADIATOR\nSYNOPSIS: Maximus is a powerful Roman general, loved by the people and the Emperor Marcus Aurelius. Before his death, the Emperor arouses the ire of his son Commodus by making public his predilection to leave the throne to Maximus. Power-hungry, Commodus kills his father, assumes the crown, and orders the death of Maximus, who manages to escape before being caught, and goes into hiding as a slave and gladiator while seeking revenge.\nAUTHOR:David Franzoni\nAVAILABLE IN: Netflix, Globoplay, Star+, Amazon Prime Video, Telecine, Youtube and Google Play")
d10 = ("HARRIET\nSYNOPSIS: Shortly after having escaped slavery, Harriet Tubman decides to help hundreds of slaves flee the South of the United States during the American Civil War, in the year 1849. Her actions give a new direction to history, and the political activist becomes a of the country's greatest heroes.\nAUTHOR: Gregory Allen Howard\nAVAILABLE IN: Amazon Prime Video, Youtube and Google Play")
